The paper discusses privacy-preserving mechanisms for analyzing data generated by smart cyber-physical systems, which involves handling large amounts of data. This suggests that the paper could belong to the cs.DB (databases) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a new data perturbation algorithm that provides a good balance between privacy and utility, which falls under the cs.CR (cryptography and security) sub-category. The algorithm is also designed to be efficient and scalable, which could place the paper under the cs.LG (machine learning) and cs.DS (data structures and algorithms) sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with data streams, which could potentially fall under the cs.CY (computational complexity) sub-category.
